<h1>Problem 1033 - 2018 IMO, P5 of 6, N</h1>
<h2 class='difficulty'>Difficulty: 7</h2>
<p>Let \(a_1,a_2,\cdots\) be an infinite sequence of positive integers. Suppose that there is an integer \(N > 1\) such that, for each \(n \geq N\), the number \[\frac{a_1}{a_2}+\frac{a_2}{a_3}+\cdots + \frac{a_{n-1}}{a_n}+\frac{a_n}{a_1}\] is an integer. Prove that there is a positive integer \(M\) such that \(a_m=a_{m+1}\) for all \(m \geq M\).</p>
